re was an absolute joke, but it would definitely fit VI's history to accidentally not mention that they beefed up the new dragon ragefire. The cleric on top should try to bring a full-blown raiding force untill we are certain that the new ragefire is still a joke, to avoid wasting spawns. (The good thing though, is if you lose this battle, you wont have to start over, since you keep your swirling pearl) At this time, Kealoha and the clerics right behind her, should she be MIA, should seek out the location of the new camp, which we'll discover when the outside-solb-Ragefire pops. At that point, when we know the new camp's location, the list rules will focus on that rare spawn.<br><br>The solb ragefire is still important, but it shouldnt fall under our list, because of the fact it will apparently spawn so often, you can stroll over to finish your epic any time you have a day to spare camping it. However, for courtesy's sake, the clerics near the top ought to be given preference for the swirling pearl untill most of the list completes this step. <p>Cayleu Starshine<br><font color = blue>Healer of Tunare</font><br><font color=red>Insidious Blood</font></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucayleustarshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cayleu Starshine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/22/02 9:08:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucayleustarshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cayleu Starshine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ragefire is my pet</span><br>  Posts: 365<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/22/02 9:36:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1067.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ALL Ragefire Clerics PLEASE READ NOW!</span><hr size=1> It has been tentatively confirmed by Test server clerics that the outside-solb ragefire will spawn in Skyfire. Not yet known if hell be a roamer, or stay put somewhere.<br><br>This could be some cruel joke, but keep an eye on skyfire. It was my guess that he'd spawn there anyway, since that zone conveniently already has red dragons.<br><br>Text from the hand-in in solb:<br><br>Zordak Ragefire stares at ***** with unblinking eyes. A wide grin crosses Zordak's face and flames flicker in the depths of his eyes. 'Welcome to the new fortress of the Plasmatic Priesthood! It's a shame about Lord Nagafen's untimely death, really it is! Such a powerful and noble creature should not perish at the hands of mortals.' ' <br>Zordak Ragefire is engulfed by a shimmering blue light! An inhuman expression of rage crosses his face and flames leap in his eyes as he begins to vanish in the shimmering light! 'The Triumvirate may have succeeded in sending me back to my cursed homeland for the time being! I swear to you I shall return from Skyfire and destroy all of the Triumvirate Missionaries in flames!' ' <p>Cayleu Starshine<br><font color = blue>Healer of Tunare</font><br><font color=red>Insidious Blood</font></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucayleustarshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cayleu Starshine</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/22/02 9:38:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugattwingreyleaf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gattwin Greyleaf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=23280381&img=5" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Will O Wisp</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/23/02 3:19:10 am)</font><br>